  "description": [
    "L T Hogan Castros Cuba Fidel Castro has been called everything from a dictator to a crazy fool by the American press Now Castro may or may not be a dictator but dont let anybody kid you hes no fool Any man who can start out with a group of eighty men to overthrow a government of almost seven million and succeed is no fool in my book Castro started a revolution for the same reason most revolutions have started since time immemorial to over throw the aristocracy In this instance the aristocracy hap pened to be Capitalism and dear reader in case you dont know it the greatest exponent of Capitalism this world has ever seen is the United States of Amer ica So the truth of the matter is that the Batista Regime an ex tremely proAmerican govern ment whom Castro and his fol lowers overthrew was not the real target of his war but only the symbol of his main objective American Capitalism Castros disenchantment with the United States did not come about overnight it was brought about by an accumulation of things built up over a period of sixty years of American intervention in Cuban affairs"
  ],
